  "prompt": "Is it possible to do MS in computer science after a bachelors degree in bioinformatics?",
  "response": "Yes, it is generally possible to pursue a Master's degree in Computer Science after completing a Bachelor's degree in Bioinformatics. Many graduate programs accept students with diverse undergraduate backgrounds, especially if they demonstrate strong analytical and computational skills. However, there may be some prerequisites that you need to meet, such as foundational courses in computer science, programming, algorithms, and possibly mathematics.\n\nIf your bioinformatics program included significant coursework in these areas, you might already be well-prepared. If not, you may need to complete additional courses either prior to or during your Master's program. It is advisable to check the specific requirements of the programs you are interested in and to reach out to the admissions offices for more detailed information.",
